ailing for Switzerland]]\n\n\n{{Switzerland-sport-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Swiss Olympic Star class sailor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{MedalTableTop|medals=\n{{Medal|Sport | [[Sailing (sport)|Sailing]] }}\n\n{{MedalCountry | {{SUI}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Olympic Games]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Star (sailboat)|Star]] }}\n\n\n{{Medal|Country | {{SUI}} }}\n{{Medal|Competition | [[5.5 Metre World Championships]] }}\n{{Medal|Gold | 2004 Torbole | 5.5m }}\n}}\n\n'''Enrico De Maria''' (born 20 December 1976 in [[R\u00fcti, Z\u00fcrich|R\u00fcti]]) is a Swiss Olympic Star class sailor. He has been crewing for [[Flavio Marazzi]] in the 2004, 2008 and 2012 Summer Olympics and finished fourth in the 2004 edition.<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/de/enrico-de-maria-1.html|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141102195342/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/de/enrico-de-maria-1.html|archivedate=2014-11-02}}</ref>\n\nHe was a grinder on [[Alinghi]] during the [[2003 America's Cup]].<ref>http://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/news/article.cfm?c_id=4&objectid=3101371</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{World Sailing|id=SUIED2}}\n\n{{Footer World Champions 5.5 Metre}}\n{{Footer European Champions Star}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:De Maria, Enrico}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Swiss male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:People from Hinwil District]]\n\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Star]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Star]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Star]]\n\n[[Category:Alinghi sailors]]\n[[Category:2003 America's Cup sailors]]\n\n[[Category:Star class sailors]]\n[[Category:5.5 Metre class sailors]]\n[[Category:World Champions in 5.5 Metre]]\n[[Category:World champions in sailing for Switzerland]]\n\n{{